body: Fixes and improves the original implementation in #500. Just to be nice, I'd suggest merging #500 first and then this one afterwards.

commit.message:
f strings: initial parsing work

Parses f-strings into ExprNodes, but with no support for compiling them. Some
known bugs are marked as TODOs.
f-strings: fix nested string literals
f-string parsing: fix bugs
f-strings: first attempt at code generation

fstrings: make conversion chars work

Still doesn't do concatenation of FormattedValueNodes correctly.

fstrings: implement concatenation using PyUnicode_Join

Using _PyUnicode_Writer might be faster but seems more complicated to implement.
f-strings: bugfixes

fstrings: fix more bugs

Not sure about the refcounting

fstrings: remove addressed TODOs

Docstrings don't support f-strings in cpython, so they don't need to here either. The scanner
seems to be working.

Current status:
- All but three of the tests from CPython's test_fstring pass. Two of the remaining ones rely
  on exec and the third relies on a runtime NameError that occurs at compile time in Cython. These
  tests still need to be added to the Cython test suite.
- I'm not overly convinced that the refcounting is correct in the C code that's currently
  emitted.
- There's some room for optimization, such as removing empty strings from JoinedStrNode,
  concatenating adjacent raw strings at compile time, and using _PyUnicodeWriter.
- Currently the feature is available in both Python 2 and Python 3 mode. It mostly works in
  Python 2, except for the !a conversion char.
Merge branch 'f_string' into f_strings_2
minor code cleanup
Py2.6 compatibility fix
add f-strings test from CPython test suite
repair issues found by CPython f-string tests
optimise internal calls to f-string parsing functions
simplify JoinedStrNode implementation by moving its substring values into a ListNode
discard empty substrings from the join-list of f-strings
reduce code overhead for common f-string formatting case without format specifier
remove need for redundant class variable
avoid formatting call overhead for simple Unicode value case
shorten test that takes excessively long to compile (with gcc)
force (re-)compilation in test regardless of previous test runs
de-optimise f-string parsing a little to fix compiled Cython
revert modified test to the way CPython spells it
make missing PyObject_ASCII() function sort-of available in Py2 (to be used by f-strings)
make f-string tests work in Py2
fix comment
disable some f-string formatting tests that give "suboptimal" results in Py2.6
special-case the substring list processing in JoinedStrNode again to reduce the number of temp vars used
whitespace
join UnicodeNode sequences in JoinedStrNode at compile time
reject f-strings for parsed cnames
move JoinedStrNode cleanup into ConstantFolding transform as that's essentially what it does
simplify code generated for f-string formatting using simple utility functions
simplify some error handling code in f-string parser
speed up character switching in f-string parser a little
set FormattedValueNode.format_spec field to None for empty format specs to simplify later "empty" tests
use standard node dispatch mechanism instead of explicit type tests in transform
unpack FormattedValueNode with constant string value at compile time (unlikely case but trivial to do...)
disable a restriction in the f-string format parser that seems arbitrary and difficult to implement
